title: For Sale:  rare collectable WWI Colt M1917, .45acp!!!!
postcontent:
Last one from my 1917 collection. Late serial number Colt, with the shouldered cylinder (not bored straight through like early model colts. Means you can shoot them without the moon clips). The finish on this piece is good, so good I couldn't believe it was original. I was told by a gunsmith that it was likely an Arsenal Refurbished gun (for WWII), but was probably never issued. I would rate the finish at a strong 97%-98%. The grips are original and correct military grips, but I have not taken them off. The bore is super bright with ZERO pitting, lands and grooves look nearly unshot. The serial number on the receiver and crane match each other, but not the grip frame (another reason I suspect arsenal refurbishing). This is a very collectable WWI revolver, in fantastic condition. 
Bluc Book is $1200...
